{"type":"message","id":"6204ea57","parentId":"e39e6af1","timestamp":"2026-05-02T02:14:24.540Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, xurl is installed. Now it says no apps registered, which is expected. I need to tell Bobby next steps - he needs to go to developer.x.com, get his API key and secret, and then run `xurl auth apps add` to register them. Then `xurl auth oauth2` to authenticate.\n\nBut I can't do the credential entry part for him. I need him to do that manually.\n","thinkingSignature":"3eb72946522bc8e95ce8da8ca1ab24cb283cdf11285946ff1adc24e10d53e125"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nDone. xurl is installed and working.\n\nNow you need to do the credential setup manually — I can't handle the API keys for you (that's by design for security). Here's what to do:\n\n**1. Go to developer.x.com** and get your API Key + API Secret from your app.\n\n**2. Run this command in your terminal:**\n```bash\nxurl auth apps add\n```\nIt'll prompt you to enter the key and secret — paste them in.\n\n**3. Then connect your account:**\n```bash\nxurl auth oauth2\n```\n\nThis opens a browser flow to authorize.\n\nOnce you've done those steps, run `xurl whoami` and tell me what it returns — I'll verify we're connected."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":101,"output":235,"cacheRead":34112,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":34448,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777688055612,"responseId":"064490f7de2ec599f53d7ac50621c954"}}
