{"type":"message","id":"14482b1f","parentId":"1e3d0a15","timestamp":"2026-05-02T02:39:23.201Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby is asking about the keys. He's seeing OAuth 1 and OAuth 2 keys on the X Developer Portal. Let me explain what he needs.\n\nThe xurl tool uses OAuth 2 by default (that's what `xurl auth oauth2` does). OAuth 2 is the more modern flow.\n\nFrom the X Developer Portal, the keys he sees are likely:\n- OAuth 1.0a (older, used for posting/likes/retweets)\n- OAuth 2.0 (more modern, used for similar things but with refresh tokens)\n\nFor xurl, he needs the OAuth 2.0 credentials (Client ID and Client Secret) to register the app with `xurl auth apps add`.\n\n\nHe should look for the OAuth 2.0 credentials section in his app settings and grab the Client ID and Client Secret from there, since that's what xurl requires for authentication.\n","thinkingSignature":"562dffab940345cbc588797f35df6f78045c43f6d6ff7efac7ba965a5ec55dc9"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n**OAuth 2.0** is what you want — that's what xurl uses.\n\nGo to your app in the developer portal and look for the **OAuth 2.0** section. You need:\n\n- **Client ID**\n- **Client Secret**\n\nThose are the two pieces. The portal might call them \"Client ID\" and \"Client Secret\" or just show them as a pair under OAuth 2.0 settings.\n\nOnce you have them, run:\n```bash\nxurl auth apps add\n```\n\nAnd it'll prompt you — paste the Client ID first, then the Client Secret."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":29737,"output":304,"cacheRead":192,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":30233,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777689550536,"responseId":"064496cf7ff094aa388036352118c21f"}}
